### GET http://localhost:7071/api/httpget
GET http://localhost:7071/api/httpget?name=TestUser

### GET with different log levels
GET http://localhost:7071/api/httpget?name=DebugTest&loglevel=debug

### GET with warning level
GET http://localhost:7071/api/httpget?name=WarningTest&loglevel=warning

### GET with error level
GET http://localhost:7071/api/httpget?name=ErrorTest&loglevel=error

### POST with JSON body
POST http://localhost:7071/api/httppost
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "TestUser",
    "generateLogs": 5,
    "simulateError": false
}

### POST to generate many logs
POST http://localhost:7071/api/httppost
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "LoadTest",
    "generateLogs": 50,
    "simulateError": false
}

### POST to simulate error
POST http://localhost:7071/api/httppost
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "ErrorTest",
    "generateLogs": 1,
    "simulateError": true
}

### Logging Demo - Shows all log levels
GET http://localhost:7071/api/loggingdemo

### Performance Test - default
GET http://localhost:7071/api/performancetest

### Performance Test - high frequency logging
GET http://localhost:7071/api/performancetest?iterations=1000&logfrequency=10

### Performance Test - low frequency logging
GET http://localhost:7071/api/performancetest?iterations=1000&logfrequency=100

### Sampling Test - generate logs to observe sampling behavior
GET http://localhost:7071/api/samplingtest?count=100

